title: Sporting Khalsa in fourth qualifying FA Cup final
text:
Khalsa at home in next phase of FA Cup 
But the game turned on its head when Ross Watson was dismissed on 30 minutes for hacking down Marvin Nisbett. 
And Nisbett dusted himself down and equalised for Khalsa on 42 minutes to give Ian Rowe’s side hope. What do you think? Be the first to comment 
Spalding were the better side with 10 men and Pemberton was forced into action. 
But Townsend’s header made the difference and Khalsa now have a tie against either Buxton or FC United of Manchester to enjoy. Receive daily email updates from the Express & Star
